### 4. FORMS & INPUT DESIGN

**Forms are where users do real work. Make them frictionless.**

**Form UX Checklist:**
```
‚ñ° Labels above inputs (not placeholder-only)
‚ñ° Logical tab order
‚ñ° Inline validation (on blur, not on every keystroke)
‚ñ° Clear required vs optional indicators
‚ñ° Helpful placeholder examples (not instructions)
‚ñ° Appropriate input types (email, tel, number, etc.)
‚ñ° Submit button disabled until form is valid
‚ñ° Success feedback after submission
```

**Validation Timing:**
- Validate on blur (when user leaves field)
- Re-validate on change if field was already invalid
- Never validate while user is actively typing

**Input Patterns:**
```jsx
// Good: Label + Input + Helper text + Error
<div className="form-field">
  <label htmlFor="email">Email address</label>
  <input 
    type="email" 
    id="email"
    placeholder="you@example.com"
    aria-describedby="email-hint email-error"
  />
  <span id="email-hint" className="helper-text">
    We'll send a confirmation to this address
  </span>
  <span id="email-error" className="error-message" role="alert">
    {error}
  </span>
</div>
```

**Password Fields:**
- Always include show/hide toggle
- Show strength indicator for new passwords
- Confirm password field for critical changes

---

### 5. NAVIGATION & WAYFINDING

**Users should always know where they are and how to get where they want.**

**Navigation Principles:**
```
‚ñ° Current location is always visible (active state)
‚ñ° Breadcrumbs for deep hierarchies
‚ñ° Back button works as expected
‚ñ° Maximum 3 clicks to any feature
‚ñ° Search available for large apps
‚ñ° Mobile: thumb-reachable primary actions
```

**Visual Hierarchy for Navigation:**
```css
/* Active nav item */
.nav-item {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  border-radius: 6px;
  transition: all 150ms ease;
}

.nav-item:hover {
  color: var(--text-primary);
  background: var(--bg-secondary);
}

.nav-item.active {
  color: var(--accent);
  background: var(--accent-subtle);
  font-weight: 500;
}
```

**Page Transitions:**
- Maintain scroll position when returning to a page
- Show loading indicator for slow transitions (>300ms)
- Animate content changes (fade, slide) for context

